  "body": "I'm working with a library which needs to be initialized in componentDidMount according to their documentation but I am not getting the expected results when I update the state, like so: \n\n``` javascript\nclass ChartContents extends React.Component {\n\n  constructor() {\n  super();\n  this.state = { stxx: {} };\n}\n  componentDidMount() {\n    let stxx=new STXChart(this.chartContainer);\n    stxx.newChart(\"SPY\", sampleData);\n    this.setState({stxx});\n    console.log(this);\n    console.log(this.state);\n}\n  render()\n   {\n     const Style = {\n       height:'600px',\n       position:'relative',\n       width:'800px'\n     }\n    return (\n      <div id=\"quickStart\" className=\"chartContainer\" style={Style}  ref={(c)=>this.chartContainer=c}></div>\n    );\n  }\n}\n```\n\nWhen I view the object in the debugger I find my state was updated on the object ChartContents with the newly created chart but when I try to access it, it returns the empty object it was initialized with. I did also see the [eslint warning](https://github.com/yannickcr/eslint-plugin-react/blob/master/docs/rules/no-did-mount-set-state.md) and I was wondering how to solve this problem. Thanks!\n\n![console](http://i67.tinypic.com/16jlxkk.png)\n",
